From b5b26d26f3a61fe0c1465003961fe632cac51054 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yousaf Chaudhry <yousafchaudhry720@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Apr 2026 11:12:50 +0500
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add PDF import support for Crystal Report Monthly
 IN-OUT

- New API route POST /api/attendance/parse-pdf uses pdfjs-dist to extract
  text with X/Y coordinates across all pages and reconstruct the attendance
  table server-side. Returns the same ParseResult shape as the Excel parser
  so Steps 2-4 of the import wizard are completely unchanged.

- Handles multi-department sections (re-detects column header per department),
  night-shift workers, employees with zero punches, and 32+ page PDFs.

- upload-dialog.tsx: accepts .pdf files; PDF path sends multipart to
  parse-pdf API, Excel path uses existing SheetJS client parser.

- next.config.mjs: adds serverExternalPackages for pdfjs-dist (Node.js only).

- Requires: npm install pdfjs-dist

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
